===Etymology===
From [[w:1250|1250]] in {{etyl|enm}} as {{term|abbeye|lang=enm||convent headed by an [[abbot]]|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|fro}} {{term|abaie|abaïe|lang=fro}}, {{term|abbaïe|lang=fro}}, {{term|abeïe|lang=fro}}, {{term|abbeie|abbeïe|lang=fro}} (Modern French {{term|abbaye|lang=fr}}) from {{etyl|LL.}} {{term|abbatia|abbātia|lang=la}}, from Classical Latin {{term|abbas|abbās|abbot|lang=la}}. See {{term|abbot|lang=en}}.

